Former Orlando Pirates defender, Justice Chabalala, has found a new home in Gqeberha. After being linked with Maritzburg United, Chabalala has joined Chippa United on a free transfer after he parted ways with the Buccaneers. Chabalala will join newly appointed Daine Klate who was confirmed by the club as head coach for the 2022/23 season. Klate will be assisted by Siya Gwambi and Bruce July in his technical team. The 30-year-old Chabalala joins Chippa from Sekhukhune United where he was on loan from an arrangement with the Buccaneers. Chabalala will be unveiled by Chippa this week, SunSport has learnt. The well-travelled Giyani-born defender was signed by Pirates in 2016 from Free State Stars, but having gone loan moves in the PSL, including Bloemfontein Celtic. The former Ea Lla Koto defender saw little game time at Sekhukhune where he made four appearances in the first round of the past season. 